@17195=~Greater Helm of Seeing~
@17196=~A more useful version of the Helm of Seeing, this helmet was the legacy of Lanasa Reesan, a powerful fighter-cleric who believed she could get particularly far into Durlag's Tower by herself. With the help of this helmet and her magic, she could easily spot any of the hidden traps and invisible ghasts that have killed many challengers of the tower. As a result, it was a danger she could see that killed her. In one hallway, she detected a crushing wall trap covering the entire passageway. There was no way to get through the hallway without triggering the trap, and there was no other path forward. Since Lanasa could not disarm traps, she could only protect herself with magic and step forward, hoping she would survive. She did not.

The Demon Knight later scavenged the helm from her corpse. In the past, the helm had been a light grey, but it has darkened after several years of being worn by the Demon Knight. It has not gained any unholy properties, though.

