@17201=~Elminster's Ecologies I~
@17202=~Elminster's Ecologies-Humanoids and Giant-kin

Written by the sage Elminster, this tome is part of a much larger body of work containing studies of strange creatures from around Toril, and some creatures from other planes. This particular book is about humanoids and giants.

One chapter describes creatures that may be found on the Sword Coast:

"Xvarts-Relatives to kobolds, xvarts have a unique power that triggers whenever they walk. It may appear as if the xvarts are teleporting from one place to another, but I have learned their power's true nature. Xvarts actually stop time for several seconds when they walk. The best way to fight xvarts would be to get close to them so they do not have to walk to you."

"Tasloi-Other relatives to kobolds, tasloi have a gaze attack. Any creature that looks a tasloi in the eye may be driven berserk, possibly attacking an ally. This will not happen if one does not make eye contact with the tasloi, or if one is more than 15 feet away."

"Hobgoblins-The supreme accuracy of the common hobgoblin with their sword is well known. Even heavy armor likely will not stop a hobgoblin. However, these creatures do not possess anywhere near the same precision with their bows. Combating hobgoblins at long range will likely be easier than fighting them up close."

"Spellcasting Hobgoblins-Some hobgoblins can also cast spells. They are unnaturally good at casting their spells, as if an archmage was casting the spell."

"Ogrillions-Although related to half-ogres, ogrillions have completely different powers. They move fast, and their punch carries enough force to knock victims approximately 30 feet away, though I have never measured the exact distance."

"Half-Ogres-The offspring of an ogre and a human, half-ogres are born with an impenetrable skin. Far better than the most perfect armor, half-ogre skin makes them nearly impossible to hit by most means. I advise using magic, which will get past their skin just fine."

"Ogres-Even these dumb brutes have powers. Ogres have abilities they can use when an opponent comes near. The ogre can either make its attacks critically effective, make itself more resistant to physical harm, release a terrifying roar, make its attacks hit with extreme force, or make its attacks slay creatures instantly. Only one of these abilities is used at a time, and it is chosen randomly, no matter which one would be the best at the time."

"Greater Ogres-These ogres are halfway to being hill giants. Unlike normal ogres, a Greater Ogre can use more than one of its abilities at once. A Greater Ogre also possesses a unique aura, which causes creatures around it to become even stupider than the ogre. This effect is thankfully only temporary."~
@17203=~Elminster's Ecologies II~
@17204=~Elminster's Ecologies-Mammals

Written by the sage Elminster, this tome is part of a much larger body of work containing studies of strange creatures from around Toril, and some creatures from other planes. This particular book is about mammals. From the introduction:

"Some druids have already written impressive texts about mammals, but those are written from a druid's perspective. This book is directed at adventurers, and is focused primarily on the dangers many mammals pose."

One chapter describes mammals that may be found on the Sword Coast:

"Rabbits-Although small and frail, rabbits possess extremely sharp teeth. They are also very lucky, as they usually have two rabbit feet."

"Squirrels-When a squirrel dies an early death, it explodes in an enormous fireball. Thankfully, few creatures attack squirrels for fear that they could be incinerated. Occasionly, though, an ogre comes across a squirrel and has a bad idea..."

"Rats-The glare of a rat causes confusion. Though rats are not much of a threat."

"Cats-Extremely resistant to physical attacks, a cat has the power to turn another creature into a rat. It can only do this once per day."

"Wild Dogs-Undomesticated dogs, these animals have the power to slow a creature, making time pass slower for it."

"War Dogs-These trained dogs have different abilities from wild dogs. Rather than slowing a creature, they can speed it up, allowing an ally to move and attack very quickly."

"Wolves-Wolves have been long known for their camouflage. They stay hidden but will reveal themselves right before they attack. Regular wolves also have the power to make their attacks critically effective."

"Dire Wolves-Bigger than normal wolves, these ones also stalk in camouflage, but their other abilities are different. After revealing themselves, they burst into a whirlwind of attacks. For regular adventurers, it is best to run away until the dire wolf stops its flurry."

"Worgs-Wolves with a more sinister streak, worgs are known for allying with goblins, who use them as mounts. Worg camouflage has a special property: any creature mounted on the worg is camouflaged along with it. Worgs can also summon another worg; the additional worg does not have this summoning ability."

"Winter Wolves-Unlike normal wolves, winter wolves turn fully invisible rather than using camouflage. They have the ability to breathe cold at other creatures; this breath weapon also temporarily makes the target more vulnerable to cold. Furthermore, once their breath reaches the target, they turn invisible again. Thus, they are only visible while their breath is on its way to the target. Though winter wolves are vulnerable to fire, the easiest way to combat them is to use magic to see through their invisibility."

"Black Bears-These bears are imbued with the power of acid. Whenever a black bear is hurt, it retaliates with a spray of acid at the attacker."

"Brown Bears-These bears crackle with electricity. Whenever a brown bear is hurt, it retaliates with a bolt of lightning at the attacker."

"Cave Bears-These bears have fire burning beneath their fur. Whenever a cave bear is hurt, it retaliates with a ball of fire centered on itself."

"Polar Bears-These bears have an affinity for cold. Whenever a polar bear is hurt, it retaliates with a cone of extreme cold at the attacker."

"Grizzly Bears-These bears are especially powerful, being imbued with multiple elements. Whenever a grizzly bear is hurt, it retaliates with a blast of fire, cold, electricity, and acid."~
@17205=~Elminster's Ecologies III~
@17206=~Elminster's Ecologies-Spiders

Written by the sage Elminster, this tome is part of a much larger body of work containing studies of strange creatures from around Toril, and some creatures from other planes. This particular book is about monstrous spiders.

"Oversized spiders have one power in common: they spawn smaller spiders when they attack another creature. This spawning is not reproduction; it is likely some innate form of conjuration magic. The smaller spiders vanish after about eight hours, as if they were unsummoned. Some of the small spiders are capable of casting spells. Most spiders (excluding Wraith Spiders) are animals, so druids and rangers will have power over them. Spiders almost never miss with their attacks."

A quick look through the book tells you there are many, many different kinds of spiders in the Realms.

"Huge Spiders-These orange spiders are poisonous, as are the spiders they spawn, but they are the weakest of the oversized spiders. Although big, they are still quite stealthy."

"Giant Spiders-These green spiders are particularly poisonous. The spiders they spawn can cast Glitterdust."

"Phase Spiders-These green spiders can teleport to other creatures, and they are among the most poisonous spiders. They spawn spiders that can cast Minor Spell Turning and can also teleport."

"Sword Spiders-These gray spiders are among the swiftest creatures in the Realms, capable of moving and attacking at unbelievable speeds. Their poison, rather than causing bodily harm, weakens the victim's reflexes. The smaller spiders they create are similarly fast."

"Wraith Spiders-These black spiders are undead. Rather than inflicting poison, these spiders inflict a disease that saps the victim's strength. The spiders they summon on hit are especially dangerous, as they can cast Harm, reducing a creature to a near-death state."

"Vorpal Spiders-These green spiders, rather than using a poisonous bite, slash with their poisonous legs. Their attacks have a good chance to decapitate the target, causing instant death (a Death Ward spell can stop this from happening). Vorpal Spiders react to being attacked by speeding up temporarily, moving and attacking faster. They are resistant to magic and physical attacks."

"Astral Phase Spiders-Often used by githyanki in their raids, these spiders have all the powers of Phase Spiders, but they also have psionic abilities."

One chapter focuses on related monsters called ettercaps.

"Ettercaps-These creatures ally themselves with spiders, and they are similarly venomous. Ettercaps are dangerous spellcasters, capable of casting multiple spells with no pause in between. The most common ettercap first casts Greater Malison twice to soften up its victims, and then casts Hold Person to paralyze them."

"Ettercap Tremor Callers-These rare ettercaps have the power to trigger earthquakes. They move in to eat once their victims are knocked down."

"Ettercap Hasteners-These rare ettercaps possess a twisted form of the spell Improved Haste, which will speed up time for a creature to such an extent that the creature quickly decays during the effect."~
@17207=~Elminster's Ecologies IV~
@17208=~Elminster's Ecologies-Monstrous Beasts

Written by the sage Elminster, this tome is part of a much larger body of work containing studies of strange creatures from around Toril, and some creatures from other planes. This particular book is about the more animalistic monsters.

Even a quick look through the book finds many desciptions of exotic monsters, such as "land sharks" whose psionic powers compel prey to walk into their enormous jaws.

Of particular interest is a chapter titled "Monstrous Beasts on the Sword Coast."

"Wyverns-Flying beasts distantly related to dragons, wyverns attack with their poisonous tail stinger. Their scales, although easier to penetrate than a real dragon's scales, will still stop most attacks. They can also breathe slippery grease, which spreads all over the ground and slows down prey fleeing from the wyvern. The wyverns can simply fly over the grease."

"Greater Wyverns-Especially large and intelligent, Greater Wyverns can cast spells. They also retaliate with a wing buffet when attacked."

"Greatest Wyverns-Among the most dangerous wyverns, Greatest Wyverns spawn a smaller wyvern with each attack they make."

"Basilisks-These 8-legged lizards have petrifying gaze. Any creature that makes eye contact with a basilisk while within 15 feet may be turned to stone permanently. Looking away from the basilisk will prevent this from happening. Basilisks are also usually protected by Stoneskin."

"Greater Basilisks-The petrifying gaze of more powerful basilisks is harder to resist. They can also cast Dispel Magic on creatures that are protected from petrification. By staying close to the basilisk, one can trick it into dispelling its own protection."

"Ankhegs-These insectoid creatures can burrow underground, and they can spit acid at their prey. Their chitinous hide provides them excellent protection. There are several different kinds of ankhegs."

"Light Ankhegs-These ankhegs spit acid especially quickly. They are smaller and frailer than other ankhegs, though."

"Heavy Ankhegs-The acid of a heavy ankheg clings to the target and continues to harm them over time. They attack slowly."

"Arcane Ankhegs-These intelligent ankhegs can cast spells. They will have to emerge from the ground to cast a spell on another creature."

"Greater Ankhegs-Each kind of ankheg has a more powerful version. Greater Light Ankhegs attack faster than their normal counterparts. Greater Heavy Ankhegs possess deadlier acid. And Greater Arcane Ankhegs have much more powerful spells. If one can find a greater ankheg and slay it, its shell could be made into a great suit of armor."

"Carrion Crawlers-Many-legged, centipede-like creatures, Carrion Crawlers attack with paralyzing tentacles. They can also cast divine spells, usually Physical Mirror, Blade Barrier and Flame Strike. However, apart from their spells, Carrion Crawlers have few defenses, and they are not very tenacious."~
@17209=~Elminster's Ecologies V~
@17210=~Elminster's Ecologies-Undead

Written by the sage Elminster, this tome is part of a much larger body of work containing studies of strange creatures from around Toril, and some creatures from other planes. This particular book is about the undead.

"Skeletons-Animated skeletons differ greatly in their powers, but most of them have a power in common: when struck, the skeleton will fall apart but its skull will remain animate. The skulls also have varying powers."

"Zombies-These walking corpses devour the brains of their victims. Most normal zombies have a common power: any creature that hits the zombie with an attack or spell gets pulled to the zombie. There are also more powerful zombies, which have much more diverse abilities."

"Ghouls-Ghouls can turn invisible, and their touch causes paralysis. Ghouls almost never miss."

"Greater Ghouls-These powerful ghouls attack and move faster, and they usually have Stoneskins. They tend to attack in groups."

"Ghasts-Stronger than ghouls but weaker than greater ghouls, Ghasts tend to wander around an area while invisible until they come close to prey or they take damage. Some ghasts can also summon other ghasts, though this summoning is silent and there may be a delay until the second ghast appears. I warn you: if you fight a ghast, expect to fight another ghast within minutes, if not within seconds!"

"Greater Ghast Lords-The most powerful undead carrion eaters, Greater Ghast Lords have a stench comparable to a Stinking Cloud, which can knock living creatures unconscious."

"Revenants-After a creature is killed in a terrible way, its soul can inhabit a body and become a revenant, determined to kill its killer. Revenants have a power that inflicts utter hopelessness on their enemies. They tend to prioritize attacking the creature against whom they have sworn vengeance."

"Vengeful Spirits-Similar to revenants but without a corporeal form, Vengeful Spirits tend to arise immediately after certain creatures die, seeking revenge on the one who just killed them. They are relatively weak, but as they are spirits, only magic or magical weapons can hurt them, and they can move through walls. Vengeful Spirits can usually cast either Spiritual Lock, which temporarily prevents a creature's mind from working (as if the creature was feebleminded), or Ethereal Retribution, which calls a flock of other life-draining spirits."

"Shadows-Spectral undead resembling humanoid shadows (except they can have height as well), shadows drain victims' strength away with their attacks. In addition, shadows can enfeeble creatures, possibly preventing those creatures from moving and making it easier to drain the last of their strength. They cannot be hit by non-magical weapons, and they can move through walls."

"Greater Shadows-More powerful than typical shadows, Greater Shadows have a particularly dangerous enfeebling ability, which weakens multiple creatures."

"Wraiths-Undead made of negative energy, Wraiths can drain the life out of multiple creatures at once by casting Soul Eater. Living creatures are harmed merely by standing near a wraith."

"Death Shades-Weak but dangerous lesser undead creatures, Death Shades seek to give living things an early death. Any creature hit by a Death Shade will die instantly unless it is protected by a Death Ward. However, Death Shades will be destroyed upon suffering even the slightest harm, and they are reckless and easy to hit. Much more corporeal than other spectral undead, Death Shades can be hurt by normal weapons, and they cannot move through walls."

"Greater Death Shades-Far more dangerous than normal death shades, these creatures can cast Wave of Destruction, a negative energy wave which can slay creatures up to 120 feet away who are not protected by a Death Ward. They are usually protected by Mirror Images and a Greater Globe of Invulerability, but they still are destroyed upon suffering any harm. They can cast Dispel Magic to dispel a Death Ward, but if you stay near them you can trick them into dispelling their own protections as well."~
@17211=~Elminster's Ecologies VI~
@17212=~Elminster's Ecologies-Constructs

Written by the sage Elminster, this tome is part of a much larger body of work containing studies of strange creatures from around Toril, and some creatures from other planes. This particular book is about golems and other constructs. From the introduction:

"Two primary categories of constructs exist. There are animated object constructs, which are usually a floating weapon or suit of armor. Then there are golems, akin to giants but made entirely of one material. Most constructs are weak to acid and blunt attacks, though there are exceptions."

One chapter describes common animated object constructs:

"Helmed Horrors-Especially intelligent, Helmed Horrors can cast the spell Disintegrate. They usually wield morningstars that make the target more vulnerable to disintegration."

"Battle Horrors-Possibly the most dangerous of the animated object constructs, Battle Horrors are animated suits of full plate armor which dual wield a flaming sword and a freezing sword. They cannot deal damage to a creature protected from both fire and cold, but they will cast Lower Resistance on such a creature. They also can make their attacks critically effective. Running from a Battle Horror is difficult, because they teleport to their enemies."

"Doom Guards-These constructs are animated suits of plate mail which wield bows, even when a creature fights them in melee. They fire piercing arrows that can hit multiple targets, and any creature hit by one of their arrows is afflicted by feelings of impending doom."

"Dwarven Doom Guards-These Doom Guards are made to look like dwarven plate armor, and they wield acidic returning throwing axes. Like other Doom Guards, they inflict feelings of doom with each hit. They are extremely resistant to all physical damage; using spells is the best option to defeat them."

Another chapter describes various golems:

"Flesh Golems-The weakest golems (though among the most intelligent), Flesh Golems move fast and punch with great force, but they are vulnerable to physical attacks, fire, and acid. If a Flesh Golem would be hit by a Flesh to Stone spell, it turns into a Stone Golem."

"Stone Golems-These golems are resistant to most physical attacks, and they can temporarily slow time for opponents. If a Stone Golem would be hit by a Stone to Flesh spell (or a Stone to Flesh Scroll), it turns into a Flesh Golem."

"Magic Golems-Made of magic itself, these golems are immune to all magic and can only be hurt by non-magical weapons. Not surprisingly, they can cast many different spells."~
@17213=~Elminster's Ecologies VII~
@17214=~Elminster's Ecologies-Slimes

Written by the sage Elminster, this tome is part of a much larger body of work containing studies of strange creatures from around Toril, and some creatures from other planes. This particular book is about slime creatures. From the introduction:

"Slimes are such varied and dangerous foes that they need their own book to describe them. Most slimes hurl balls of their own slime at enemies with unfailing accuracy. Attacking a slime usually causes a piece of itself to discharge at the attacker, as if the slime had attacked that creature."

One chapter describes slimes that can be found on the Sword Coast:

"Green Slimes-Among the weaker slimes, Green Slimes cover targets in poisonous slime. They cannot be hurt by missiles or electricity."

"Gray Oozes-Gray Oozes hurl gray slime with crushing force. Targets can be stunned and knocked back. They are weak to fire and cold."

"Ochre Jellies-These slimes can knock victims unconscious with their attacks. They are very resistant to all damage, but they are actually most vulnerable to physical damage."

"Mustard Jellies-Attacks from a Mustard Jelly can poison, slow, blind and deafen creatures. They are resistant to magic and physical attacks, but they have no resistance to fire or cold."

"Fission Slimes-These slimes will split in two if they are killed without having been hit by a fire attack. They can only be hurt by fire and physical attacks. Their own attacks are acidic, and they also make creatures more vulnerable to acid."

"Dense Puddings-These slimes split whenever they are hit by fire or electricity. They can only be safely hurt by physical attacks. A Dense Pudding's attacks inflict a disease that saps victims' constitution and slows them."

"Gelatinous Spheres-Quite different from most other slimes, Gelatinous Spheres are transparent and very difficult to see unless one has walked inside one. They corrode anything they touch and any creature inside them. In addition, creatures inside them will become more vulnerable to acid."~
