@19010=~Spiritual Hammer
(Invocation)

Level: 2
Sphere: Combat
Range: 0
Duration: 3 rounds
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

By calling upon Tempus, Branwen brings into existence a magical hammer, which she can use for the duration. As with her priest spells, Branwen counts as eight levels higher than normal when using this innate ability. As a result, the hammer she summons is more powerful. At levels 1 to 4, it is a +2 weapon. At levels 5 and above, it is a +3 weapon. The Spiritual Hammer uses the warhammer proficiency. Like a war hammer, the Spiritual Hammer deals 1d4+1 base damage (plus enchantment bonuses), but it can also be used to attack enemies from far away. When it is swung from far away, the hammer still counts as a crushing weapon, not a missile weapon. It does not get any penalties when swung at a foe in melee range.~
