After casting this spell, the caster's next attack against a creature inflicts a necrotic chill. This deals 5d4 magic cold damage, and the target must Save vs. Death or lose 3 points of Strength for 5 rounds. The Strength loss is cumulative; if the creature is reduced to 0 Strength, it dies instantly. On a critical hit or a backstab, the damage and Strength loss are doubled, unless the critical hit or backstab is averted. The wizard gets a +5 bonus to hit the target, but if <PRO_HESHE> misses, the spell is wasted. In addition, the touch attack itself does 1d2 fist damage (Strength bonuses apply, as does any effect that increases the damage of unarmed attacks). The touch attack counts as a +6 weapon for purposes of determining what it can hit. The wizard only has one charge, and once an opponent has been touched, the spell's energies have been used. The wizard gets a +10 bonus to hit the target, but if <PRO_HESHE> misses, the spell is wasted. An undead creature suffers no damage or Strength loss from Chill Touch, but will be affected by panic for 2 turns unless it successfully makes a Save vs. Death.~
