@22292=~Dismiss

Casting Time: 0

The ability Dismiss allows Tiax to push another creature away from him. For two rounds, the target creature will constantly be pushed away from Tiax. This ability has extremely long range, and Tiax can use this ability even if he cannot see the target.

Tiax can use this ability at will.~
@22293=~Attain Perfection

Casting Time: 9

This ability temporarily makes the character perfect in every way. For 1 turn, the character's Strength, Dexterity, Constitution, Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma are all set to 25. The character can potentially use this time to equip items with high stat requirements.~
@22295=~Global Domination

Casting Time: 40

Global Domination, Tiax's ultimate ability, allows him to take control of every creature in the entire plane for five rounds. There is no Saving Throw, and even undead and constructs are affected; only Magic Resistance can prevent the effects of this ability. The creatures themselves do not realize that they are being controlled by Tiax, and creatures outside the current area will go about their lives as normal unless they are specifically given commands by Tiax. Tiax can also see through the eyes of multiple creatures dominated this way, though there is a maximum number of independent sets of senses he can process at once. Global Domination is not a hostile act; creatures will not be hostile after the effect ends unless they were initially hostile or they were attacked during the effect.~
@22297=~Guardian Eyes

Casting Time: 0

As a paladin of Helm, Ajantis has the power to turn other people into guards, regardless of their willingness. After using this ability on a humanoid, Ajantis is able to see through that person's eyes and see what he or she sees for 2 hours. This ability can be cast even on hostile humanoids who are unwilling to assist Ajantis in any way, though this ability alone does not allow Ajantis to control the target. Guardian Eyes is not a hostile act; it will not turn neutral creatures hostile. There is no Saving Throw, and Magic Resistance cannot stop this ability. The range of this ability is not limited by Ajantis' visual range. Guardian Eyes can only affect humanoids and giant humanoids.

Ajantis can use this ability at will.~
@22300=~Expertise

The Expertise ability allows the character to fight defensively at the cost of accuracy. The character can choose to gain up to +5 AC as well as a THAC0 penalty of the same size. Expertise cannot be dispelled.

This character can use this ability at will.~
@22301=~Improved Expertise

The Improved Expertise ability allows the character to fight defensively at the cost of accuracy. The character can choose to gain up to +9 AC as well as a THAC0 penalty of the same size. Improved Expertise cannot be dispelled.

This character can use this ability at will.~
@22302=~Critical Boon

Casting Time: 0

This ability allows the character to bestow the effects of Critical Strike upon a creature of <PRO_HISHER> choice. For 1 round, every attack the target makes is an automatic critical hit, regardless of the roll.~
@22303=~Secret Swap

Casting Time: 0

The character instantly switches places with another creature. The character can use this even if the target is on the other side of the area (though they must be in the same area), or if the target is hidden or invisible.

This character can use this ability at will.~
@22304=~Darts of Bone
(Necromancy)

Level: 6
Range: 0
Duration: 5 rounds
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: The caster
Saving Throw: None

This spell creates nine darts that can be used by the caster and cannot be unequipped so long as the spell is in effect. The darts are +3, do 1d4+3 missile damage with +3 to hit, and a creature struck by a dart must Save vs. Death at -6 or take 2d6 magic damage and have its Strength reduced by 3 for 5 rounds. Strength reduction is cumulative, and hitting a single creature with multiple darts can potentially reduce its Strength to 0, killing it instantly. Undead, constructs and extraplanar creatures are immune to the magic damage and Strength reduction from these darts. The caster gains proficiency in darts as long as <PRO_HESHE> has at least one dart remaining, unless <PRO_HESHE> already has a higher level of proficiency in darts.

This character can cast this spell at will.~
@22306=~Red Metamagic

Casting Time: 0

By using Red Metamagic, the Red Soul can amplify the damage of <PRO_HISHER> spells even further, but at great danger. As long as this ability is active, any non-physical damage dealt by the Red Soul is increased by 100% rather than by 50%. However, the Red Soul also becomes extremely vulnerable to all damage and cannot gain any damage resistances while this ability is active. Once used, Red Metamagic can be disabled at any time as a free action.

The Red Soul can use this ability at will.~
@22307=~Green Metamagic

Casting Time: 0

While using Green Metamagic, non-physical damage dealt by the Green Soul is not halved, but it has the opposite effect, healing instead of dealing damage. For example, an Agannazar's Scorcher spell, rather than dealing a total of 3d6 damage, will heal the targets by a total of 6d6 hit points. Once used, Green Metamagic can be disabled at any time as a free action.

The Green Soul can use this ability at will.~
@22309=~Perfect Clone

Casting Time: Instant

Using this ability, Glint creates a copy of himself that is almost completely identical to him. The clone is at the same level as Glint and has all of Glint's spells and abilities except for Perfect Clone. The clone is not an illusion but rather a flesh-and-blood perfect duplicate of Glint. For 8 hours, the clone will serve the party with the utmost loyalty.

The ability has not casting time, can be used immediately after another ability, and can be used while the game is paused.~
@22310=~Glint's Irresistible Spin

Casting Time: 0

Upon using this ability, Glint forces a creature to spin in place for 8 hours. The creature will do nothing other than repeatedly spin in place, even if it sees enemies. There is no Saving Throw, and the creature's Magic Resistance makes no difference. If the creature takes damage, the effect will end. Whether or not the effect ends early, the creature cannot be affected by Glint's Irresistible Spin for 8 hours from the time the ability was used. This ability has extremely long range, and Glint can use this ability even if he cannot see the target.

Glint can use this ability at will.~
@22311=~Black Blade of Disaster
(Evocation) 

Level: 9
Range: 0
Duration: 1 round/level
Casting Time: 4
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

This spell enables the caster to create a black, blade-shaped planar rift about three feet long. It jumps into the caster's hand and is used as a normal sword, remaining there for the duration of the spell. The caster is considered to be proficient to the point of Grand Mastery in this weapon. The sword acts as a +5 weapon and deals 2-24 damage to its victims. Also, every time it hits a target, the victim must make a Save vs. Death at +4 or be disintegrated. There is also a 10% chance with every hit that the sword drains 4 levels from the target and heals the wielder 20 Hit Points.~
@22312=~Xzar's Vampiric Touch

Casting Time: 3

When this spell is cast, the target loses 1d6 Hit Points for every 2 caster levels, to a maximum drain of 6d6 for a 12th-level caster. These Hit Points are added to Xzar's current Hit Points, with any Hit Points over Xzar's normal maximum treated as temporary additional Hit Points. The temporary Hit Points last for 1 hour. If Xzar casts his signiture Vampiric Touch multiple times, the temporary Hit Points will stack.

Xzar can use this ability at will.~
@22329=~Wave Blessing

Casting Time: 0

By using Wave Blessing, Tenya empowers the target's next critical hit. The next time the blessed creature makes a successful critical hit, it instantly casts Smashing Wave on the creature it hit. After that happens, or after 7 rounds have passed, the effect ends. If the critical hit is averted, the wave will not be released, but the effect will not end yet.~
@22330=~Smite Boon

Casting Time: 0

This ability allows the character to bestow the effects of Smite upon a creature of <PRO_HISHER> choice. For 1 round, every attack the target makes is an automatic critical hit, regardless of the roll. In addition, for 2 rounds, every attack the target makes will cause knockback and stun for 1 round (a successful Save vs. Paralysis negates the stun but not the knockback).~
@22332=~Kill

Casting Time: 0

By using this ability, Vynd instantly kills a single creature that has 60 Hit Points or less. There is no Saving Throw, though Magic Resistance can prevent the effects. Kill can be cast instantly and requires no words or gestures to use.

Vynd regains this ability 3 rounds after using it.~
@22333=~Globe of Blades

Casting Time: 3

This ability creates of globe of whirling blades surrounding the character. Every 2 seconds, each creature within 4 feet of the character takes 1d6 slashing damage with no Saving Throw. The character can end the effects of Globe of Blades at any time. Otherwise, the globe lasts permanently and cannot be dispelled.

This character can use this ability at will.~
@22337=~Greater Shield of Lathander
(Conjuration)

Level: 7
Sphere: Guardian
Range: Visual range of the caster
Duration: 3 rounds
Casting Time: 0
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: None

This spell grants the recipient 100% Magic Resistance and immunity to damage for the duration of the spell. Evil creatures cannot be protected by a Greater Shield of Lathander. This spell can only be cast by good-aligned characters.

Gavin's version of Greater Shield of Lathander can be cast instantly and at long range.~
@22339=~Stinking Cloud
(Evocation)

Level: 2
Range: Visual range of the caster
Duration: 1 turn
Casting Time: 2
Area of Effect: 15-ft. radius
Saving Throw: Neg.

When casting Stinking Cloud, Korax creates a billowing mass of nauseous vapors up to 90 ft. away from its position. Any creature caught within the cloud must roll a successful Saving Throw vs. Poison at +2 or be sent reeling and fall down for 1d2 rounds. Those who make successful Saving Throws can leave the cloud without suffering any ill effects, although those remaining in the cloud must continue to save each round. A Dispel Magic will remove the nausea on a particular character, but if they remain in the cloud, then they are still subject to its effects.

Korax can cast Stinking Cloud at will.~
@22340=~Invisibility
(Illusion/Phantasm)

Level: 2
Range: 0
Duration: 24 hours
Casting Time: 0
Area of Effect: The caster
Saving Throw: None 

This spell causes Korax to vanish from sight and be undetectable by normal vision or even infravision. Of course, Korax is not magically silenced, and certain other conditions can render it detectable. Items dropped or put down by Korax become visible. The spell remains in effect until it is magically broken or dispelled, until Korax attacks any creature, or until 24 hours have passed.

Korax can cast Invisibility at will.~
@22342=~Superflail

Casting Time: 3

By using this ability, Will gives a creature a Superflail, which replaces the creature's previous weapon for 15 rounds. The Superflail is a +12 flail, which attacks for 1d12+12 damage and gets +12 to hit. It gives the wielder proficiency in flails if <PRO_HESHE> is not already proficient.~
@22343=~Supercrush

Casting Time: 0

By using this ability, Will causes a creature to experience a crushing blow of immense power from an invisible force. The creature takes exactly 60 crushing damage. There is no Saving Throw, Magic Resistance cannot prevent it, and the damage bypasses the creature's Crushing Resistance.~
@22347=~Hop

Casting Time: 0

Alora instantly teleports to any location within 10000 feet that the party is aware of.

Alora can use this ability at will.~
@22353=~Greater Wizard Eye
(Divination)

Level: 6
Range: Visual range of the caster
Duration: 1 hour
Casting Time: 9
Area of Effect: Special
Saving Throw: None

A much more potent version of Wizard Eye, this spell creates an invisible, ethereal eye. The caster can see anything the eye sees. The eye can see invisible or ethereal creatures, and its visual range is increased significantly. It can also move through walls: simply click on a point anywhere on the map, and the eye will float to that point, passing through normally impassable obstacles in the way.~
@22358=~Mimic Spell

Casting Time: 0

Imoen has the ability to copy a spellcaster's incantations and gestures perfectly, regardless of whether she understands them. In mimicking a spell, she chooses two creatures, one of which must be casting a spell. She then casts a copy of that spell on the other creature. If both creatures are casting spells, Imoen mimics the second creature's spell and casts it on the first creature. She can use this ability either to double an ally's spell or to give an enemy spellcaster a taste of their own medicine.

Imoen can use this ability at will.~
@22370=~Elemental Weapons

This ability lets the character imbue their weapons with a particular kind of element or energy: fire, cold, electricity, acid, or magic. While the ability is active, the base damage type of the character's weapons is changed to the chosen damage type. For example, a sword could be altered to deal fire damage rather than slashing damage. Altered weapons will still gain damage bonuses from Strength or abilities (if any); the bonus damage will also be of the new damage type. This ability lasts until it is turned off by using it again and selecting the option to turn it off.

This character can use this ability at will.~
@22378=~Shapeshift: Ankheg

Ellyrian has the ability to turn into an ankheg. As an ankheg, she can aerate the soil and increase crop yields, but unlike normal ankhegs, she would never eat a farmer's livestock.

Strength: 18/00 unless higher
Dexterity: 16 unless higher
Constitution: 20 unless higher

Base Armor Class: -4 (-7 vs. slashing, -5 vs. piercing and missile)
Number of Attacks: 1
Attack Damage: 1d4 missile, +10d4 acid damage over 4 rounds (Save vs. Breath for half), strikes as a +4 weapon

Special Abilities:
- Acid Resistance: +50%
- When not attacking or casting a spell on another creature, Ellyrian can burrow underground.

Ellyrian can use this ability at will.~
@22381=~Whirlwind Boon

Casting Time: 0

This ability allows the character to bestow the effects of Greater Whirlwind Attack upon a creature of <PRO_HISHER> choice. For 1 round, the target's attacks per round are set to 10.~

@24000=~The spell reveals no information about the target.~
@24001=~Cows are very heavy but are great at jumping! Once per round, a cow can jump very high and land on a creature, dealing 4d6 crushing damage with a Save vs. Breath for half.~
@24002=~Hulrik's cow is very large and fat, even for a cow. She's probably too heavy to jump as other cows can, but she can take much more punishment. For some reason, she is able to move during Time Stop, even if someone else casts it.~
@24003=~As a paladin of Helm, Ajantis can see invisible creatures and cannot be backstabbed. He has some very useful innate abilities and mastery in several weapons.~
@24004=~Alora is extremely good at all thieving skills, partly due to her amazing luck and partly due to her Dexterity. She has Aura Cleansing and can teleport anywhere on the map and switch places with any creature.~
@24005=~Baeloth is a powerful sorcerer with many innate abilities, and since he is a Drow, he has 50% magic resistance. He can cast 3 additional spells of each spell level,  His special ring gives him Aura Cleansing and lets him cast his spells instantly, but it also causes his spells to target the wrong creature.~
@24006=~Branwen is a priestess whose divine spells are greatly enhanced. Branwen is considered to be 6 levels higher for purposes of determining the power of her divine spells.~
@24007=~Coran is one of the few fighter/bounty hunters. He has permanent Free Action, immunity to wing buffet and pulling effects, a +70% Set Traps bonus, and a +50 bonus to Saves vs. Polymorph. He moves at the fastest speed possible, and whenever he moves to a point, he instantly teleports himself to his destination.~
@24008=~Dorn has deadly, dark powers, given to him by a demon named Ur'Gothoz. He heals himself whenever he kills a creature. His Save vs. Spell is terrible, though.~
@24009=~Dynaheir is almost completely immune to fire and gets +10 to hit and damage with her fists (and with touch attacks such as Shocking Grasp). More notably, she is considered to be 6 levels higher for purposes of determining the power of her mage spells.~
@24010=~Edwin can cast twice as many spells of all spell levels. This also doubles the additional spells from his amulet and his specialist kit. He can cast spells of every level, from 1st to 9th.~
@24011=~Eldoth is proficient in all weapons and fighting styles. He can use any item, though he won't be able to cast spells or pick pockets while wearing heavy armor. He is immune to poison and has a +50 bonus to Saves vs. Wands.~
@24012=~Like all Shadow Druids, Faldorn has Aura Cleansing and knows a special 4th level spell called Lightning Storm. She has a +50 bonus to Saves vs. Spell.~
@24013=~Garrick applies the effects of his bard song to all nearby allies (this will stack with his actual bard song). Garrick's level is increased by 10 for purposes of determining the power of his mage spells, but his spells take longer to cast. He knows every mage spell of 1st and second level, and he has a special 3rd level spell called Garrick's Flame Arrow.~
@24014=~Imoen can attack 5 times per round no matter what weapon she's using. She is immune to acid, and acid damage will actually heal her. Her Phantom Blade allows her to attack and backstab at long range.~
@24015=~Jaheira is a Harper. A strong character all around, she is a master of several weapons and fighting styles. Her maximum hit points are increased by 60.~
@24016=~Kagain is one of the sturdiest characters around. His maximum hit points are increased by 120, and he has 100% resistance to magic damage as well as various other resistances. He gains +1 to all saving throws for every 20000 gold the party currently has, to a maximum of +10 to all saves at 200000 gold or more.~
@24017=~Khalid is a Harper. He has grandmastery in all weapons, though he cannot obtain any proficiency in fighting styles. He can cast spells while wearing heavy armor, and he is immune to any effect that would disable his spellcasting, such as Silence or Miscast Magic. He is permanently hasted (this haste is not negated by Free Action) and can do things while time is stopped regardless of who stopped it. He has great Saves vs. Breath but terrible Saves vs. Death.~
@24018=~Kivan gets +6 to hit with missile weapons (this stacks with the bonuses from the archer kit), and his critical hit chance with missile weapons is increased by 30%. He can see farther than normal, allowing him to attack enemies before they can see him. He gets +20 to hit against half-ogres. He is great at finding traps.~
@24019=~Minsc deals maximum damage with each hit and attacks with zero Speed Factor regardless of his weapon. He has +50 to Saves vs. Death and his maximum hit points are increased by 40.~
@24020=~Montaron is a member of the Zhentarim. All poison damage he deals is increased by 50%. He can use all his abilities instantly if he wishes.~
@24021=~Neera has Aura Cleansing, and she counts as 11 levels higher for purposes of determining the power of her spells. However, every spell she casts triggers a wild surge. Neera is highly resistant against some damage types and very weak against others. She can cast Ruby Ray of Reversal on herself to turn her weaknesses into resistances and vice versa.~
@24022=~Quayle is the greatest of geniuses, and he knows almost every non-necromancy mage spell of 4th level or lower. He can turn himself invisible at will and can target partially invisible creatures with spells.~
@24023=~Rasaad is a master of precise blows: he has a +20 THAC0 bonus, and he can hit even on a roll of 1. He can create a Searing Orb at will.~
@24024=~Safana has a base AC of -10. She can charm humanoids at will, and she can also use the ability Avoid Death to temporarily prevent herself from being reduced below 1 HP.~
@24025=~Shar-teel is a grandmaster of many weapons. She gets +5 to hit and damage with melee weapons. However, her armor class can't be modified except by Dexterity and weapon styles.~
@24026=~Skie's backstab multiplier is reduced by 1, but she backstabs with every hit.~
@24027=~Tiax has Aura Cleansing. He is almost completely immune to electricity and he has +100% to Detect Illusions and can see invisible creatures. He can push and pull creatures at long range at will, and he can temporarily dominate the world once per day.~
@24028=~During the day, Viconia has a 50% chance of spell failure, but during the night, she can cast all of her spells and abilities at will, as long as she successfully casts them. She has a backstab multiplier of x2.~
@24029=~Xan is excellent at wielding his moonblade, and every attack he makes with a melee weapon is a critical hit. With ranged weapons, he gets a critical hit on a roll between 15 and 20.~
@24030=~Xzar is a member of the Zhentarim. Like all Zhentarim necromancers, Xzar has Aura Cleansing. Xzar in particular is also almost completely immune to cold. He can use life drain and level drain abilities at will.~
@24031=~Yeslick's casting time is decreased by 10 for all of his spells and abilities, allowing most of them to be cast instantly. Every spell he casts targets all creatures within 15 feet. He is specialized in all weapons a cleric can use. He never gets tired, even after casting Greater Restoration.~
@24032=~The tutors are harmless, though they are always teleporting around randomly. Since putting on clothes while teleporting around is really difficult, the tutors wear a single set of clothes their whole life. Don't worry, it's not as bad as it sounds, because the tutors DO wash and clean their clothes; they just do it while they're wearing them. They need to bathe in a very large bathtub to avoid accidentally teleporting out of the tub. That problem might be avoided if they bathed in a much large body of water like a river, but alas, there are no rivers in Candlekeep. Although there is certainly a large body of water outside of Candlekeep, the problem is that if the tutors left Candlekeep they would have to present a tome of great value to the Keeper of the Portal to get back in. Most of the tutors can't do that, because they gave their only acceptable tome the first time they entered Candlekeep. Now you might be thinking, why don't they just stand at the walls and have their random teleportation teleport them through? There are two problems with that idea, unfortunately. One is that the walls are too thick to teleport through with the short distance that they teleport with that ability. The other is that the walls of Candlekeep are enhanced by special wards that prevent people from teleporting through them. The tutors will have to contend with bathing in bathtubs and occasionally teleporting out of them and getting the floor wet.~
@24033=~Firebead Elvenhair knows two spells, Flame Arrow and Flesh to Stone. He is a nice person, and if he sees you under attack by an evildoer, he might help you out. Also, if you talk to him 30 times, he will give you 300 gold.~
@24034=~Gantolandan is asleep. He will probably wake up if you attack him. Whenever Gantolandan gets hit by an attack or spell, he summons an efreeti. The efreeti is under his control.~
@24035=~Whenever Gantolandan gets hit by an attack or spell, he summons an efreeti. The efreeti is under his control. Gantolandan's efreet help him in his thieving endeavors.~
@24036=~Garan is a terribly thuggish mage who casts Imprisonment on people who anger him. He tends to carry around at least one scroll of Freedom at any given time. Like most ankheg trainers, he has 120% resistance to acid.~
@24037=~Gellana Mirrorshade has two spells: Champion's Strength and Cause Critical Wounds. If she sees a warrior in your party fighting an evildoer, she might cast Champion's Strength on him or her.~
@24038=~Gibberlings move very fast, have great THAC0, and attack six times per round. However, they don't have many Hit Points, they are extremely easy to hit, and they have terrible saving throws. They also take double damage from fire. Even as simple a tool as a torch could kill a gibberling.~
@24039=~Diseased Gibberlings are some of the weakest monsters around, almost as weak as Lesser Kobolds. It would be embarrassing for an adventurer to get killed by one of these. Like all gibberlings, they take double damage from fire.~
@24040=~Garclax's Minor Globe of Invulnerability protects him against a lot of spells. However, if you can overcome the globe, he has the same terrible saving throws every gnoll has.~
@24041=~Whenever Ludrug takes damage, he teleports to the source of the damage, and he dispels all dispellable effects on himself. If he were smarter he would have realized that he could intentionally injure himself to dispel harmful effects on himself while out of combat. Or perhaps he knows that and just doesn't want to. Ludrug also has the same terrible saving throws that every gnoll has.~
@24042=~Gnoll Elites have 50% resistance to all physical damage, so it is even less of a good idea to fight them in melee than it is with other gnolls. However, they are also even more vulnerable to magic than other gnolls are. Not only do they have the same terrible saving throws as all gnolls, they are also 100% weak to fire, cold, electricity, acid and magic damage.~
@24043=~A Gnoll Chieftain can cast a single Web spell, which it uses to assert authority over other gnolls, whose terrible saving throws prevent them from escaping the web. The chieftain itself is normally immune to the web due to its Minor Globe of Invulnerability. If the chieftain's protection were to be removed, it could get stuck in its own web.~
@24044=~Gnoll Slashers automatically get a critical hit on each attack. However, they actually have fewer Hit Points than normal gnolls.~
@24045=~Gnoll Veterans have 99% Missile Resistance and many Hit Points. They can cast the Power Word, Stun spell, though they don't have the wisdom to use it effectively. They will cast it on the first enemy they see, even if that creature has more than 90 current Hit Points.~
@24046=~Gnolls are savage fighters, dealing 3 very accurate, damaging attacks per round. However, their saving throws are terrible.~
@24047=~Flinds are immune to fire, and they have an ability that deals fire damage to a creature and pulls them to it. Like all gnolls, they have terrible saving throws.~
@24048=~Britik is one of the scarier gnolls. His halberd deals bonus damage against panicking creatures. However, he does have a gnoll's standard terrible saving throws.~
@24049=~Ingot has 100% resistance to missile and magic damage, but is 50% weak to fire, cold, electricity and acid. He is a dangerous fighter with a very powerful halberd.~
@24050=~This is a rakshasa pretending to be Irlentree. The real name of this creature is Juskal.~
@24051=~This is a rakshasa pretending to be Zorl. The real name of this creature is Shalak.~
@24052=~Zordral is an aspiring acid-mage. In battle, he lowers his foe's acid resistance before casting his signiture spell Zordral's Corrosive Breath.~
@24053=~All zombies drain their victims' Intelligence on hit. In addition, any creature that hits them gets pulled to them.~
@24054=~Zal is the fastest dart thrower on the Sword Coast, capable of throwing 10 darts per round. He is a member of the Blacktalons and as such he gets +20 to hit with ranged weapons. Zal in particular relies so much on his darts that he will throw them at point blank instead of switching to a melee weapon.~
@24055=~Whenever an xvart moves, it stops time for 2 seconds. It regains this ability after 4 seconds. When fighting an xvart, it is wise to face it in melee combat, since it will not stop time if it is standing in place and attacking. An xvart attacks 5 times per round and can move and attack while time is stopped, regardless of who stopped it.~
@24056=~Arral the Shade Master summons a Lesser Death Shade whenever he gets hit. Also, whenever he gets hit, he casts Mass Invisibility. This will turn his Lesser Death Shades invisible.~
@24057=~Alenis Xvartfoot stops time whenever he moves, just like an xvart does. Alenis stops time for a longer period of 1 round, and he regains the ability after 1 round.~
@24058=~Sorar can attack in a Cone of Cold with his Huge Flail of Frost. He cannot do any damage to a creature that's immune to cold. He himself is immune to both cold and magic cold, though he is 50% weak to electricity.~
@24059=~Glansh is a fighter/mage, and here is his strategy. At the beginning of combat, he puts on Stoneskin and Minor Globe of Invulnerability. The first spell he casts is Blood Rage. The second spell he casts is Shadow Door, which turns him invisible, most likely causing the berserk creature to attack one of their allies. While invisible, he will cast Improved Alacrity, then he will cast five Lightning Bolt spells in a row. He will then cast Improved Haste and Tenser's Transformation, and he will attack.~
@24060=~Kolik has 99% resistance to all damage types. If he takes damage, he summons an Invisible Stalker. Even still, Kolik dreads taking damage, because he doesn't have many Hit Points. His wail can cause people to die.~
@24061=~The fists of Ustier the Plated Monk will trigger the effects of Bigby's Clenched Fist.~
@24062=~If you are reading this, you shouldn't have much trouble killing Finim, if that's what you want to do.~
@24063=~Rannick Demonfinger can summon Greater Glabrezus at will, though he has no way of protecting himself against them. Although he can certainly put up a fight, he is afraid to fight most of the time because he's worried he could get killed by his demons.~
@24064=~Rassul the Detonater likes to blow his enemies up with his arrows. He tends to carry one Arrow of Detonation and one Blue Arrow of Detonation with him at all times. He is immune to fire and cold. He always uses his bow, even at point blank.~
@24065=~Sargern is a priest of Cyric. In battle, first he casts Greater Command twice. Then he casts Hold Person once. Then he casts Cause Serious Wounds twice. Finally he casts Animate Dead four times. If he is below 50% of his health, he casts Cure Serious Wounds, which he can do twice. Whenever he casts a spell, he automatically casts Animate Dead. He can automatically see and target invisible creatures.~
@24066=~Orach is very hard to hit, as he has an Armor Class of -26. He can use Enrage, but only once. After that wears off, he is vulnerable to mind-affecting spells.~
@24067=~Neth Sederavan is a fighter with some spellcasting abilities. First he casts Damage Turning. Then he casts Globe of Invulnerability. Finally he casts Imprisonment on one of his enemies. If he is in combat but he doesn't see an enemy or none of his enemies are close enough to him, he teleports to one before casting Imprisonment. Then he attacks.~
@24068=~Whenever Jalos hits someone with an attack, they get stunned for 3 seconds with no saving throw. He would make a powerful ally if you charmed him!~
@24069=~A Blacktalon Elite is an expert archer whose arrows almost never miss. Like all Blacktalons, the elites get +20 THAC0 with ranged weapons. A Blacktalon Elite will switch to melee weapons (which are much less dangerous) if an enemy gets too close.~
@24070=~This basic Iron Throne mercenary is a skilled fighter with poor saving throws.~
@24071=~This elite Iron Throne mercenary is a very skilled fighter with mediocre saving throws.~
@24072=~This guard tries to rush his enemies and attack too quickly to handle, but he doesn't have many Hit Points.~
@24073=~This guard is an excellent archer (though not as excellent as a member of the Blacktalons) who can attack 5 times per round. If you get up close to him, he switches to a melee weapon but not before using War Cry.~
@24074=~This is a member of the Blacktalons who decided to work directly for the Iron Throne. He starts with two skins of Stoneskin on, deals high damage, gets +20 THAC0 with missile weapons, and has protection from Time Stop. He can use Greater Whirlwind Attack but only once; if you run away until it wear off, he won't be able to use it again. Barring extraordinary circumstances, he only has 19 Hit Points, making him a prime target for Power Word, Sleep.~
@24075=~Gorion is a powerful mage who has never met his match. He is immune to knockback effects such as wing buffet; this really helped him when he and his colleagues fought a rampaging red dragon. They defeated the dragon, though it managed to escape before they could kill it.~
@24076=~This is not Gorpel Hind; this is a greater doppelganger!~
@24077=~This is not Farluck; this is a doppelganger!~
@24078=~This is not Nelik; this is a doppelganger!~
@24079=~This is not Turpin; this is a doppelganger!~
@24080=~This bartender is a doppelganger! If you buy a room from it, remember to check your room from traps and rig an alarm system to make sure that no one will assassinate you in your sleep!~
@24081=~This waiter is a doppelganger!~
@24082=~This guard is a doppelganger!~
@24083=~This prostitute is actually a doppelganger!~
@24084=~This cook is actually a doppelganger!~
@24085=~This merchant is actually a doppelganger! You bet that all these Iron Throne merchants are doppelgangers!~
@24086=~This is not Shelligh; this is a doppelganger! You wonder what the doppelganger did to the real child. Hopefully he isn't dead...~
@24087=~This is not Kolssed; this is a doppelganger! After Gorion died, you had heard a fit of horrible, doppelganger-like laughter. Maybe it was from him!~
@24088=~This bat is actually a doppelganger! But surely you expected that.~
@24089=~This is not Dillar; this is a doppelganger!~
@24090=~This commoner is actually a doppelganger!~
@24091=~This nobleman is actually a doppelganger!~
@24092=~This noblewoman is actually a doppelganger!~
@24093=~The Coquetle butler is actually a doppelganger! Who knows what insidious plans it has in store for Mr. Coquetle?~
@24094=~This traveler is actually a doppelganger!~
@24095=~Algernon is wearing a cloak which appears to be magical. He is also a doppelganger!~
@24096=~This is not Gorion; this is a doppelganger!~
@24097=~This is not Tethtoril; this is a doppelganger!~
@24098=~This is not Elminster; this is a fire elemental!~
@24099=~This horse is actually a doppelganger! Though that shouldn't be a surprise by this point.~
@24100=~These poisonous snakes are created by the Asp's Nest darts. They are a real pain in the asp.~
@24101=~The Bothersome Sentries are constructs in Durlag's Tower that get imprisoned when they take damage.~
@24102=~A Lesser Death Shade has 1 HP and an Armor Class of 20. It has -28 THAC0 and when it hits a creature it deals 50% of its maximum HP rounded down.~
@24103=~Phlydia is a very forgetful mage, but luckily she still remembers some of her spells. The spells she has are Ray of Enfeeblement, Melf's Acid Arrow, and Magic Missile, and she casts them in that order. She is a nice person and is willing to cast spells on your behalf if she sees an evildoer attacking you.~
@24104=~This is Anoobergaran, a juvenile brass dragon. Currently he is shapeshifted as a human, but he will reveal his true form if attacked. Although his talkativeness can be irritating at times, he is a creature of good, and the world will not look highly upon you if you kill him.~
@24105=~Anoobergaran has a very large number of Hit Points, an extremely high Armor Class, impenetrable Saving Throws, 50% Fire Resistance, and 20% Magic Resistance. He can see invisible creatures. When he is reduced below 25% HP, he can cast Heal, but only once. He can use his aura of fear once per turn, his wing buffet once per three rounds, and his breath weapon once per six rounds.~
@24106=~This is not Golin Vend; this is a greater doppelganger!~
@24107=~Genthore is a durable fighter who can cast Critical Strike once per day. He likes to wield axes that are especially deadly on a critical hit, such as the Beruel's Retort throwing axes, which can disintegrate foes on a critical hit. If you run away when he uses his Critical Strike and return once it wears off, he will become much less dangerous.~
@24108=~No wonder this cat wasn't killing the rats.~
@24109=~A Doom Guard fires 10 arrows per round, and it has a virtually infinite supply of them. It is immune to fire, cold, electricity, acid, poison, magic fire, magic cold, and magic damage. It has 99% resistance to all physical damage, so most physical attacks will deal 1 damage. Barring extraordinary circumstances, a Doom Guard has only 3 hit points. It is unaffected by the Legacy of Bhaal. It can move during Time Stop regardless of who stopped time. A Doom Guard is a kind of golem, and as such it is immutable. This means that its resistances cannot be changed, it has +50 to Saves vs. Polymorph, and it is immune to disintegration and polymorph effects. Legend has it that there is a special hammer somewhere in the world that can remove the immutability of golems.~
@24110=~A Battle Horror is immune to missiles, poison, and magic damage. It has 99% resistance to all other damage, so most attacks will deal 1 damage. Barring extraordinary circumstances, a Battle Horror has only 7 hit points. It is unaffected by the Legacy of Bhaal. A Battle Horror's flaming sword will cause Slow for 5 rounds (Save vs. Wands at -8 negates). It can move during Time Stop regardless of who stopped time. A Battle Horror is a kind of golem, and as such it is immutable. This means that its resistances cannot be changed, it has +50 to Saves vs. Polymorph, and it is immune to disintegration and polymorph effects. Legend has it that there is a special hammer somewhere in the world that can remove the immutability of golems.~
@24111=~A Helmed Horror is immune to missiles, poison, and magic damage. It has 99% resistance to all other damage, so most attacks will deal 1 damage. Barring extraordinary circumstances, a Helmed Horror has only 7 hit points. It is unaffected by the Legacy of Bhaal. A Helmed Horror's morningstar gives a cumulative -4 penalty to Save vs. Polymorph with each hit, and it will cast Disintegrate on a creature that has worse than 15 Save vs. Polymorph. It can move during Time Stop regardless of who stopped time. A Helmed Horror is a kind of golem, and as such it is immutable. This means that its resistances cannot be changed, it has +50 to Saves vs. Polymorph, and it is immune to disintegration and polymorph effects. Legend has it that there is a special hammer somewhere in the world that can remove the immutability of golems.~
@24112=~Hobgoblins get +20 to hit, but only with melee attacks (including melee weapons with long reach, such as Phantom Blade and Spiritual Hammer). Spellcasting hobgoblins count as twenty levels higher for purposes of determining spell power.~
@24113=~Hobgoblin Elites, like all hobgoblins, get +20 to hit with melee weapons and +20 caster level with all spells. Hobgoblin Elites in particular can cast Bless, but they know no other spells.~
@24114=~Chill Hobgoblins, like all hobgoblins, get +20 to hit with melee weapons and +20 caster level with all spells. Chill Hobgoblins in particular can cast Melf's Acid Arrow but nothing else. Chill Hobgoblins have a tendency to go invisible but they have no idea why.~
@24115=~Hulrik can move during Time Stop, regardless of who uses it. This has saved his life from marauding xvarts on multiple occassions. His cows, on the other hand, haven't been so lucky. Some of them are also unaffected by Time Stop, but they cannot run away fast enough.~
@24116=~Hurgan Stoneblade is a level 25 dwarf warrior, almost the peer of Durlag Trollkiller but not quite. He has 25 Strength, Dexterity and Constitution, 25% Magic Resistance, 50% resistance to all physical damage, and flawless saving throws. He moves extremely fast.~
@24117=~Icharyd is a dreadful wraith that wields the Spectral Brand. It has a cursed ring that allows it to regenerate 1 hit point per second but gives it -100% physical damage resistance. Icharyd has 50% Fire Resistance, 50% Electricity Resistance, 75% Acid Resistance, and 75% Magic Damage Resistance, in addition to the normal immunity to cold and poison. In battle, Icharyd will first cast Wild Horror and then cast Slay Living. After that, it will attack.~
@24118=~Ike Cascadion Vendar will lead you on a tour of Durlag's Tower, but don't expect him to take you very far in. He also tries to sell adventurers wardstones for the tower, but his wardstones are fake. Don't buy them.~
@24119=~Izefia is an avenger who harnesses the power of spiders. In battle, he will buff himself, cast Web multiple times, and turn into a sword spider. Regardless of his form, he is immune to Web effects.~
@24120=~Jacil is an extremely sturdy fighter, possessing 25 Constitution and at least 318 hit points. However, he takes double damage from physical attacks. Each time he is hit by an attack or spell, the attacker is subject to the spell Dolorous Decay.~
@24121=~Jardak is immune to all damage. However, he can be made vulnerable by lowering his resistances.~
@24122=~Jebadoh has 60% electricity resistance and at least 36 hit points. Anyone who dares deal damage to him will be smitten by Talos Lightning. Hopefully he will never get into a fight with the other fishers, as that could end very badly...~
@24123=~Telmen has 40% electricity resistance and at least 48 hit points. Anyone who dares deal damage to him will be smitten by Talos Lightning. Hopefully he will never get into a fight with the other fishers, as that could end very badly...~
@24124=~Sonner has 80% electricity resistance and at least 60 hit points. Anyone who dares deal damage to him will be smitten by Talos Lightning. Hopefully he will never get into a fight with the other fishers, as that could end very badly...~
@24125=~A Gray Ooze is extremely strong and can hurl slime with force enough to stun victims and knock them back if they fail a Save vs. Breath at +4.

Like all oozes, a Gray Ooze has amazing saving throws, it is immune to backstabs and critical hits, its attacks automatically hit, and it gets a free attack against any creature that hits it.~
@24126=~A Mustard Jelly's attacks are poisonous and will inflict blindness, deafness and slow unless a Save vs. Breath is made at -2.

Like all oozes, a Mustard Jelly has amazing saving throws, it is immune to backstabs and critical hits, its attacks automatically hit, and it gets a free attack against any creature that hits it.~
@24127=~A Greater Green Slime attacks ten times per round, but otherwise its attacks are the same as that of a normal Green Slime. Its attacks force the target to make a Save vs. Poison or be poisoned, taking 20 damage over 1 turn.

Like all oozes, a Greater Green Slime has amazing saving throws, it is immune to backstabs and critical hits, its attacks automatically hit, and it gets a free attack against any creature that hits it.~
@24128=~An Ochre Jelly knocks creatures unconscious for 1 round with each of its attacks (Save vs. Breath at -5 negates). Thankfully, it can only attack once per round.

Like all oozes, an Ochre Jelly has amazing saving throws, it is immune to backstabs and critical hits, its attacks automatically hit, and it gets a free attack against any creature that hits it.~
@24129=~A Fission Slime launches acid that lowers the target's Acid Resistance by 50% for 1 turn (after dealing damage). A Fission Slime must be hit with fire before it dies, otherwise it will split.

Like all oozes, a Fission Slime has amazing saving throws, it is immune to backstabs and critical hits, its attacks automatically hit, and it gets a free attack against any creature that hits it.~
@24130=~A Green Slime's attacks force the target to make a Save vs. Poison or be poisoned, taking 20 damage over 1 turn.

Like all oozes, a Green Slime has amazing saving throws, it is immune to backstabs and critical hits, its attacks automatically hit, and it gets a free attack against any creature that hits it.~

@24131=~Schlumpsha attacks with exploding acidic slime that deals 4d4 acid damage to all creatures within 30 feet and lowers the acid resistance of those creatures by 20% for 8 hours. In addition, Schlumpsha has a stunning Psionic Blast ability, which he can use up to three times per day. He can also see invisible creatures.

Like all oozes, Schlumpsha has amazing saving throws, he is immune to backstabs and critical hits, his attacks automatically hit, and he gets a free attack against any creature that hits him.~
@24132=~A Dense Pudding attacks with slime that deals high damage, slows the target, and saps the target's strength with a disease that lasts for 8 hours. Furthermore, if it is hit with a fire or electrical attack, it will split.

Like all oozes, a Dense Pudding has amazing saving throws, it is immune to backstabs and critical hits, its attacks automatically hit, and it gets a free attack against any creature that hits it.~
@24133=~Tarnor is a dwarven lesser hero. He can use Smite once per day. He is immune to poison and wing buffet.~
@24134=~When damaged, Stephan will undergo an explosive transformation into a Burning Wizard. He won't be much of a threat if you don't attack him.~
@24135=~This sword was created by a Mordenkainen's Sword spell. It can attack at long range with high accuracy, but only once per round.~
@24136=~Don't tell anyone, but if you kill Reginald, you will gain 100000 experience.~
@24137=~Ratchild is a Greater Kobold priestess. She has good saving throws and can cast all of her spells instantly. She starts by casting Hold of Person. Then she casts Harm, and finally she casts Bolt of Glory three times. If she detects a party member who is invisible, she will cast True Seeing. Ratchild is actually not the child of a rat.~
@24138=~Raleo Windspear has the ability to cast Creeping Doom at will. He used this ability to great effect in his short adventuring career. Raleo also has many hit points, amazing saving throws and high resistances.~
@24139=~Furret is looking to sell a Gem of Seeing. The gem is real and may be worth the money.~
@24140=~Silke is a high-level bard. She has a special bard song that deals damage to all enemies within 15 feet equal to 25% of their maximum Hit Points (rounded down). It has no effect on creatures immune to magic damage. In combat, she will sing her bard song in between casting spells while walking toward her enemies. When she is below 50% of her maximum HP, she will cast Mislead, and the clone will sing Silke's bard song as well.~



@28001=~Sirene has a massive amount of Hit Points, but she takes double damage from physical attacks. She regenerates 1 hit point per second.~
@28002=~Tenya's casting time is decreased by 10. All crushing damage she deals is increased by 50%, including crushing damage from spells such as Smashing Wave. She can cast certain water-themed druid spells, such as Smashing Wave and Call Water Weirds.~
@28003=~Dave can cast many lightning and/or storm-themed spells: Chain Lightning (as a 2nd-level spell), Call Lightning, Lightning Bolt, Lightning Storm, Static Charge, Ball Lightning (as a 4th-level spell), and Fire Storm, Acid Storm and Storm of Vengeance as 5th-level spells. All electricity damage he deals is doubled, and all fire, cold and acid damage he deals is increased by 50%. He can cast Energy Blades at will.~
@28004=~Flara has comparable stats to an actual dragon: she has many Hit Points, a base Armor Class of -11, 25 Strength, and 100% fire resistance. She is immune to backstab and can see invisible creatures.~
@28005=~Littlun is permanently under the effects of Improved Haste. She can see through the eyes of any creature she has hit with a ranged attack in the last round.~
@28006=~Moidre's critical hit chance is increased by 25%. She can use Improved Power Attack, Improved Expertise, and Globe of Blades at will.~
@28007=~Vynd's backstab multiplier is increased by 2, and he has +60% Hide in Shadows and Move Silently. Whenever he takes damage, he goes invisible for 1 round, leaving a clone in his place. Every 3 rounds, he can kill a single creature that has less than 60 Hit Points.~
@28008=~Finch can cast an additional spell of each spell level, and she can cast twice as many priest spells of each spell level (this also doubles her additional spell). She can cast learn new priest spells (e.g. spells at high levels) by casting them from scrolls. She gains three times as many stat bonuses from reading stat-increasing books. ~
@28009=~Gavin counts as 6 levels higher when using Turn Undead. During the morning and during the day, his priest spells have quadruple the normal duration. In addition, during the morning, his caster level is increased by 11.~
@28010=~Arkanis has grandmastery in warhammers and crossbows. His weapons always deal crushing damage rather than their base damage type. He has many useful abilities, including Smite and Stoneskin, both of which he can cast multiple times.~
@28011=~Canderous can attack and cast spells at any creature he sees, regardless of the normal range of the weapon or spell. He can also cast spells at any creature seen by another party member or by his special Wizard Eye. However, enemies can attack and cast spells at him at long range as well.~
@28012=~Deder has maximum proficiency in all fighting styles, and he is at least proficient in every weapon. He can use any item. His signiture ability Deder's Arsenal lets him instantly create a magical weapon of his choice to wield.~
@28013=~Mordaine's casting time is decreased by 10. She can reflect spells, absorb spells, and knock back creatures at will, and she can grant immunity to fire, cold, electricity, acid, and/or magic damage. She can also foretell the name of any spell another creature is casting.~
@28014=~Osprey can cast both cleric and druid spells. Her wizard and priest spells have double the normal duration.~
@28015=~Indira regains a previously-cast spell of 2nd-level or lower whenever she hits a creature with an attack. If that attack was a critical hit (and the critical hit was not averted), she regains an additional spell of 4th-level or lower. She can cast Black Blade of Disaster as an innate ability.~
@28016=~All fire, cold, electricity, acid, poison and magic damage dealt by Emily is increased by 75%. She has 50% resistance to fire, cold, electricity and acid. She can use Stunning Attack more times per day than just about any other character.~
@28017=~Whenever Drake casts a spell, he also casts a copy of that spell on himself (regardless of whether the spell is beneficial or harmful). He can regain all of his spells and abilities by resting for 3 rounds.~
@28018=~Like other ghouls, Korax has -20 base THAC0, 0 base AC, multiple attacks per round, and can turn invisible at will. He can also cast Stinking Cloud at will. He summons another (normal) ghoul whenever he kills a creature.~
@28019=~Will is a grandmaster of flails. He has a special bard song that grants +2 to hit and damage, with an additional +4 to hit and damage for party members who are wielding a flail. He can create a Superflail once per day, and he can deal 60 damage to a creature once per day. He can also use Mass Cast to apply his spells or abilities to multiple creatures.~
@28020=~Vienxay cannot backstab, but she has her own equivalent: if she casts a spell while invisible or stealthed, she casts the spell twice. In addition, while invisible or stealthed, she moves significantly faster, is hasted, and can cast spells instantly. All cold and magic cold damage she deals is increased by 50%.~
@28021=~Kale's Strength bonuses to hit and damage are doubled, and the extra bonuses apply to both melee and ranged weapons. He regains 2 hit points whenever he takes damage.~
@28022=~Verr'Sza has permanent Aura Cleansing and is immune to all spells of 3rd-level or below unless he is the source of the spell. He can use all of his Naztharune abilities at will.~
@28023=~Aura can use any item. She creates potions as a very high-level artificer. She can create a wand once per week.~
@28024=~Ishlilka dispels all effects on any creature she hits with a critical hit. She has some great abilities, including Protection from Magical Weapons.~
@28025=~Mur'Neth automatically succeeds on all saving throws. He can turn into a Mustard Jelly and gain most abilities of a Mustard Jelly, including the ability to hit automatically and get a free attack upon being hit by an attack or spell.~
@28026=~Helarine counts as 6 levels higher when using Turn Undead. All magic damage she deals is increased by 50%, and all healing from her spells is increased by 50%.~
@28027=~Whenever White is hit by an attack or spell, he gains the effect of Improved Haste for 1 round. If he goes berserk, he remains controllable but gains all the benefits of the berserk effect. He can give himself a single Stoneskin at will.~
@28028=~Whenever one of Valerie's spells deals damage, it deals an extra die of damage if the target is evil. All creatures have an additional -2 penalty to saves against Valerie's spells.~
@28029=~Isra gets an additional 5% critical hit chance for every 1 Charisma she has over 15. She deals an additional 2d6 magic fire damage with each weapon hit.~
@28030=~Ellyrian can entangle any creature she hits with a melee or ranged attack. All healing or regeneration from her spells and abilities is increased by 100%. She can shapeshift into an ankheg at will.~
@28031=~Helga has +10 luck. She regains a previously-cast spell of 2nd-level or lower whenever she hits a creature with an attack. If that attack was a critical hit (and the critical hit was not averted), she regains an additional spell of 4th-level or lower.~

